Serialized Form

  • Package com.squareup.leakcanary

    • Class com.squareup.leakcanary.AnalysisResult extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • leakFound

          boolean leakFound
          True if a leak was found in the heap dump.

        • excludedLeak

          boolean excludedLeak
          True if AnalysisResult.leakFound is true and the only path to the leaking reference is through excluded references. Usually, that means you can safely ignore this report.

        • className

          java.lang.String className
          Class name of the object that leaked if AnalysisResult.leakFound is true, null otherwise. The class name format is the same as what would be returned by Class.getName().

        • leakTrace

          LeakTrace leakTrace
          Shortest path to GC roots for the leaking object if AnalysisResult.leakFound is true, null otherwise. This can be used as a unique signature for the leak.

        • failure

          java.lang.Exception failure
          Null unless the analysis failed.

        • analysisDurationMs

          long analysisDurationMs
          Total time spent analyzing the heap.

    • Class com.squareup.leakcanary.LeakTrace extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • elements

          java.util.List<E> elements

    • Class com.squareup.leakcanary.LeakTraceElement extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • referenceName

          java.lang.String referenceName
          Null if this is the last element in the leak trace, ie the leaking object.

        • type

          LeakTraceElement.Type type
          Null if this is the last element in the leak trace, ie the leaking object.

        • holder

          LeakTraceElement.Holder holder

        • className

          java.lang.String className

        • extra

          java.lang.String extra
          Additional information, may be null.

        • fields

          java.util.List<E> fields
          List of all fields (member and static) for that object.
